Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Watson, out Caught by Bairstow!! Watson is walking! No century but hasn't he put on a show tonight or what! Was a good short ball from Bhuvneshwar and Watson got rushed on the pull. There was a definite top edge as it went through to Bairstow who took a stunning one-handed catch, diving to his left. The umpire was probably blinded and didn't know what to do. Watson did the right thing, would have been out anyway if SRH reviewed this. Ends a sensational knock from one of IPL's and T20 cricket's legend. Watson c Bairstow b Bhuvneshwar 96(53) [4s-9 6s-6]

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Raina, out Stumped!! Walks right past the googly, didn't have a clue about it! Fuller length from Rashid, pitched around middle and Raina was looking to work it through the on-side, expecting a leg-break. But he's wrong.
